{
    "PageTitle": "display memory-monitor information",
    "FuncDef": "The display memory-monitor information command displays the memory overloading status of boards.",
    "CLIs": [
        "display memory-monitor information { slot <slot-id> | all }"
    ],
    "ParentView": [
        "All views"
    ],
    "ParaDef": [
        {
            "Parameters": "slot slot-id",
            "Info": "Specifies the slot ID of a board whose memory overloading status is displayed.\n-"
        },
        {
            "Parameters": "all",
            "Info": "Displays the memory overloading status of all boards.\n-"
        }
    ],
    "Examples": [
        [
            "<HUAWEI> display memory-monitor information all",
            "Memory overload information                                                     ",
            "--------------------------------------------------------------------            ",
            "Slot       Time                     State                                       ",
            "--------------------------------------------------------------------            ",
            "1          0000-00-00 00:00:00      Unoverload                                                ",
            "--------------------------------------------------------------------"
        ],
        [
            "<HUAWEI> display memory-monitor information slot 1",
            "Memory overload information                                                        ",
            "--------------------------------------------------------------------            ",
            "Slot       Time                     State                                       ",
            "--------------------------------------------------------------------            ",
            "1          0000-00-00 00:00:00      Unoverload ",
            "--------------------------------------------------------------------"
        ]
    ],
    "ExtraInfo": "Usage Scenario\nWhen the memory usage is high, run the display memory-monitor command to check whether memory is overloaded. If memory is overloaded, the administrator can take action to reduce the memory usage and ensure that the device runs properly.\nThe display memory-usage command can be used to display the memory usage.\nPrecautions\nIn VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS."
}